Dear Cyril (We feel we can call you that because we’re still in holiday mode): The honeymoon is over. We say that because it’s been two years since you effectively toppled Jacob Zuma as leader of the ANC and president of our country and, while we have deep sympathy for the challenges you face in turning around an organisation (and government) filled with incompetents and thieves; we’ve heard enough of your talk. It’s time to walk the walk. Your New Year’s address to the nation was, we are afraid to say, more of the platitudes we’ve heard over and over...